      "url": "https://refractor.io/biology/hybrid-rods-cones-eye-cell-deep-sea-fish-vision/",
      "title": "[New Atlas] A strange new eye cell is rewriting how vision works",
      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://assets.newatlas.com/dims4/default/fef29da/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1200x630+0+85/resize/1200x630!/quality/85/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnewatlas-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F9a%2F503e47034337811e0e5ffc0b27e6%2Ftwo-pearlside-species-that-have-hybrid-photoreceptors-in-their-eyes-as-larvae-and-adults-maurolicus-muelleri-and-maurolicus-mucronatus.jpg&amp;rf.image_optimisation=0\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<p><img alt=\"Two pearlside species that have hybrid photoreceptors in their eyes as larvae and adults, Maurolicus muelleri  and Maurolicus mucronatus\" src=\"https://assets.newatlas.com/dims4/default/3bd5fc8/2147483647/strip/true/crop/1200x799+0+0/resize/1200x799!/format/webp/quality/85/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnewatlas-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F9a%2F503e47034337811e0e5ffc0b27e6%2Ftwo-pearlside-species-that-have-hybrid-photoreceptors-in-their-eyes-as-larvae-and-adults-maurolicus-muelleri-and-maurolicus-mucronatus.jpg\" /><p>For more than 150 years, vertebrate vision has been understood as a two-part system: rods for low-light conditions, and cones for bright light and color. That tidy division is now under the microscope, as researchers from the University of Queensland have discovered a new hybrid cell that breaks the rule: rod-shaped photoreceptors that run cone-specific genetic programs.</p><p><a href=\"https://refractor.io/biology/hybrid-rods-cones-eye-cell-deep-sea-fish-vision/\">Continue Reading</a></p><p><b>Category:</b> <a href=\"https://refractor.io/biology/\">Biology</a>, <a href=\"https://refractor.io/science/\">Science</a></p><p><b>Tags:</b> <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/vision/\" rel=\"tag\">Vision</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/fish/\" rel=\"tag\">Fish</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/university-of-queensland/\" rel=\"tag\">University of Queensland</a></p>",
      "date_published": "2026-04-13T14:02:00+00:00",
      "authors": [
        {
